      "text": [
        " رَجُلٍ اِسْتَعَارَ ثَوْباً ثُمَّ عَمَدَ إِلَيْهِ فَرَهَنَهُ فَجَاءَ أَهْلُ اَلْمَتَاعِ إِلَى مَتَاعِهِمْ فَقَالَ \"يَأْخُذُونَ مَتَاعَهُمْ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4085 - Aban narrated from Hariz, from Abu Abdullah (as), regarding a man who borrowed a garment and then intentionally used it as collateral for a loan.\nImam (as) said: \"The owners of the item have the right to reclaim their property.\""
        ]
      }
    },
